Russia’s Gutseriev to Invest in Belarus Potash Plant, Belta Says

-- B y   A l i a k s a n d r   K u d r y t s k i
-- 
2011-10-05T16:40:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/russia-s-gutseriev-to-invest-in-belarus-potash-plant-belta-says.html
GCM Global Energy Plc, controlled by
Russian businessman Mikhail Gutseriev, plans to invest in a $1.5
billion project to build potash plant in  Belarus , Belta
 reported , citing Prime Minister Mikhail Myasnikovich.  The plant will be the country’s second for production of
the soil nutrient and will have a capacity of 1.1 million metric
tons a year, Myasnikovich said during a meeting with Gutseriev
in Minsk today, according to the state-run news service. The
plant may be fully operational in 2021 and add 1,500 jobs,
Myasnikovich said, cited by Belta.  Gutseriev’s press service declined to comment when called
by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aliaksandr Kudrytski in Minsk, Belarus at 
 akudrytski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
